## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of historical data and the complexity of economic factors involved. Different historians and economists offer varying interpretations of the events, which can lead to conflicting conclusions. Additionally, the focus on American economic recovery may not fully represent the global impact of World War II on the Great Depression. Further research could explore the international dimensions of the economic recovery during and after the war.